<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-03-10T12:40:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-03-10T12:40:00-05:00" n="267" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d267">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1088.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Sullivan</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-10T13:00:00-04:40">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 10, 1914, 1 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>There is no question in my judgment but that the $500,000 will enable
                            Dominican Government to live and enact the reforms suggested by you.
                            Hasten appointment of commercial attaché.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>